Not sure if anyone else is having this problem but it steals my gems. Twice I purchased the pack of 60 and when I get come to choice that would put me below 10, it takes the gems but doesnt unlock the choice and tells me to buy more. It's quite frustrating seeing as how I'm paying for these gems only to have them taken away for no reason. That being said, I like the animations and I was a fan of the previous season. I like the characters and the story so far. They just need to fix the gem issue. Edit: Fusebox did update the game and I no longer have this issue. This game is fun so far. The characters have good personalities and There's already more drama than there was in S3. That being said, there could be more free clothing choices along with more hairstyles, but overall I like the new way of customizing your character. I like that I can change my hairstyle mid episode. What I don't like about this season is how many choices cost gems. There's a few times I've noticed that one choice to do something costs 10 gems and if you move past it, the same choice pops up a second time that also costs 10 gems, even if you unlock it the first time. It doesn't make sense to have 2 of the same choices cost gems back to back. I'm also not a huge fan of having to wait an entire week just for a few episodes that seem shorter than they used to be. It doesn't turn me off from the game but it'd be nice to at least have maybe two updates a week. I've enjoyed the game so far regardless of all that and I'm excited to see what they do with the rest of season. I enjoyed the other seasons immensely and I can't wait to win the 50k again!
